# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in your OpenRouter key.
# Get a key at https://openrouter.ai/keys

OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...

# Optional — used for OpenRouter attribution headers
OPENROUTER_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Model routing (per-role). Override with any model id from https://openrouter.ai/models
# See docs/MODELS.md for the rationale + alternatives. Paste current slugs if these 404.
# Premier config uses THREE distinct families so the audit is a real cross-family check.
MODEL_SCORING=anthropic/claude-opus-4.8          # the judge: validation, refine, deep bull/bear/reconcile
MODEL_WRITING=google/gemini-3-flash-preview      # cheap/fast: evidence queries + ranking, chat, deep CoVe
# Second-family AUDIT judge — scores the same prompt as a cross-family Goodhart check
# (divergence >15/criterion is SURFACED, never averaged into the score). MUST be a
# DIFFERENT family from MODEL_SCORING. GPT-5.1 is the pick: reliable long-JSON, and a
# third family (Anthropic scorer + Google CoVe + OpenAI audit) for maximum independence.
MODEL_AUDIT=openai/gpt-5.1                        # deep mode, every 3rd auto-iterate round, calibrate

# Self-consistency scoring samples per validation (k parallel scoring calls; per-criterion
# median). Opus is a strong single-sample judge, so 2 cuts noise without k=3's cost; use
# 3 with a weaker/cheaper scorer, 1 for single-sample. Deep-validation mode ignores k
# (it runs its own bull + bear + reconcile + CoVe pipeline, ~3-4x a standard call).
SCORING_SAMPLES=2

# Optional — Reddit API for the evidence pipeline. Without these, evidence comes from
# Hacker News only and the report shows a "Reddit not connected" hint.
# Create a free "script" app at https://www.reddit.com/prefs/apps and paste its id/secret.
#REDDIT_CLIENT_ID=
#REDDIT_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Optional — path to the Chrome/Chromium the PDF export drives (puppeteer-core). Defaults
# to the macOS Google Chrome location; set this if yours is elsewhere or you're not on a Mac.
#CHROME_PATH=/Applications/Google Chrome.app/Contents/MacOS/Google Chrome
